The paper proposes a novel transfer learning based dynamic multi-objective optimization algorithm that uses regression to predict objective values. This algorithm falls under the category of machine learning and optimization, which is covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. The most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper heavily relies on machine learning techniques. The second likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the paper deals with optimization problems that require intelligent decision-making. The third likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as the paper proposes an evolutionary algorithm for solving dynamic multi-objective optimization problems. The fourth likely sub-category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), as the paper deals with optimizing systems with multiple conflicting objectives. The fifth likely sub-category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), as the paper proposes an algorithm that can be parallelized to improve its performance.
